Vice President Pence visited Ecuador and expressed gratitude for the warm welcome and hospitality. He commended President Moreno for his leadership and commitment to strengthen the relationship between Ecuador and the United States. Pence announced that the US will provide $1.5 million to support Ecuador's efforts in combating corruption and strengthening civil society. He also discussed the importance of cooperation in addressing security threats such as drug trafficking and criminal organizations. Pence highlighted the ongoing crisis in Venezuela and expressed support for efforts to restore democracy and provide aid to Venezuelan migrants. President Moreno thanked Pence for the visit and emphasized the common interests between the two countries, including economic development, security, and combating transnational crime. He expressed concern for the situation of Latin American children separated from their parents and the humanitarian crisis in Venezuela. Both leaders called for peaceful dialogue and respect for human rights in Nicaragua. They expressed a commitment to work together to strengthen bilateral relations.